On Tuesday, May 08, 2007, at 04:44PM, "Martin Strandgard" <mnstra(-at-)unimelb.edu.au> wrote:

>What head temps did you have before all the changes? The only times I 
>have seen head temps above 400 deg F have been due to vacuum leaks (I 
>have a 2l 76 camper stock except weber prog). 

It's easy to exceed 400F going highway speeds even with 17" of vacuum. Some data I recorded two summers ago:

MPH RPM CHT 
 50 2620 340F 
 55 2860 360F 
 60 3150 380F 
 65 3440 380F 
 70 3720 400F 
 75 4010 420F 

If you go uphill and try to maintain those speeds, the temps increase even further.

